headline: Ralph Lauren Stock Rises on Earnings.  Management Is Upbeat.
summary: Ralph Lauren  stock was rising Thursday after the company yet again proved the brand’s resilience in a weak environment for luxury goods, issuing better-than-expected quarterly results and raising its financial guidance for the full year.  Ralph Lauren reported adjusted earnings of $3.79 a share for its second fiscal quarter, the three months through September, compared with the consensus call for $3.45 among analysts tracked by  FactSet  Fewer discounts and lower cotton prices helped boost profits this quarter, the company said.  Adjusted for foreign currency fluctuations, revenue grew by 14% from the year-ago quarter.

headline: Eli Lilly, Novo to cut GLP-1 cost; airline stocks fall on FAA cut
summary: Yahoo Finance's John Hyland tracks Thursday's top moving stocks and biggest market stories in this Market Minute. Eli Lilly (LLY) and Novo Nordisk (NVO) will lower GLP-1 prices as a result of newly made agreements with the Trump administration. Airline stocks, including United (UAL), American (AAL), and Delta (DAL), are falling after the FAA announced a 10% decrease in flight traffic amid the government shutdown. Ralph Lauren (RL) stock is under pressure even after the company reported second quarter results that topped analyst estimates. Stay up to date on the latest market action, minute-by-minute, with Yahoo Finance's Market Minute.
